			<b>Series Connection</b><br />
			<ol>
                <li>
                    Connect three solar cells in series. Measure the open circuit voltage.
                </li>
                <li>
                    2.	Connect a potentiometer to the output of the series connection shown in Figure 3. 
                    Connect the voltage meter in parallel with the solar cells, and the current meter in series to measure the output voltage and current respectively.
                </li>
                <center>
                    <img alt="fig3-seriesParallelSolarCells" class="img-responsive" id="headerMainImage" src="~/images/experiments/seriesParallelSolarCells/figure3.png">
                    <p>Figure 3: Solar Cells in Series.</p>
                </center>
                <li>
                    Vary the value of the potentiometer from 50Ω to 3000 Ω with an interval of 50 Ω. Use the voltmeter and ammeter to measure the output voltage and current. 
                    Record the voltage and current characteristic on the plot (x axis is current, y axis is voltage).
                </li>
			</ol><br />
			<b>Parallel Connection</b><br />
