                   Connect three solar cells in parallel. Measure the open circuit voltage
                </li>
                <li>
                   Connect a potentiometer to the output of the parallel connection shown in Figure 4.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Vary the value of the potentiometer from 20 Ω to 4000 Ω with an interval of 10 Ω to 100 Ω. Use the voltmeter and ammeter to measure the output voltage and current.
